title: Nuclear Charge Dispersion in the High-Energy Fission Of Uranium.

x4freetext: Nuclear Charge Dispersion in the High-Energy Fission

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Canadian Journal of Physics, Vol.41, p.762 (1963)

x4freetext: The Uranium Target Foil /47.5 Mg/Cm**2 Approximately/
Was  Sandwiched  Between  Two  Similar  Foils  to Guard
Against Recoil Losses and Irradiated Downstream from  a
Monitor  Foil  Similarly  Guarded and Carefully Aligned
The Errors Quoted are Standard Deviations Compounded
From Estimated Errors in Decay Curve Analyses,Counter
Of +-10% in the Accepted Values of the Monitor Cross
Sections was Included in the Cs-136,Rb-86 and Niobium
Standard Deviations,But not in Those For the Other
Cesium Nuclides,Which were Measured Relative to Cs-136.
The Relatively Large Errors in the Cs-130 Cross Section
Were Due to Its Very Low Yield in this Energy Region,
And Those in the Cs-137 Values are a Reflection of Its
Long Half-Life and the Difficulty of Measuring the 660-
KeV Photopeak in the Presence of Cs-134.
The Independent Formation Cross-Sections of Cs-135
And Cs-137 have Been Interpolated from Charge
Dispersion Curves and Reported in Table 16.
Small Corrections For Self-Absorption in the 4-Pi
The Correction For the Self-Absorption of 134-M-Cs
